{
  "doc_id": "30758",
  "text": "Total fecal collection was utilized to validate the chromium release rate from the continuous release bolus [CITATION_1] . Six steers were harnessed with fecal bags and received the same bolus as administered to the steers used for the determination of intake. Steers were gathered twice daily, and fecal collection bags were removed and weighed to determine content. Feces from fecal collection bags was subsequently mixed and subsampled for analysis. Rectal grab samples were taken during the morning collection. All fecal samples were oven dried in a 60°C forced air oven, ground through a 1-mm Wiley mill screen, and stored until analysis. Chromium concentrations in the feces were determined using the method described by [CITATION_2] . Forage intake was then estimated by dividing fecal output by indigestibility of the forage diet.",
